 a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705207,"age":95,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705208,"age":97,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Joane Howles was born in 1490, in Rustington, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. She married John Cooke I in 1505, in Rustington, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died about 1597, in England, at the age of 108."},"et":{"1490–about 1597":"1490–umbes 1597","1480–1578":"1480–1578","1506–1582":"1506–1582","1490–1597":"1490–1597","1582":"1582","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1558":"1558","1578":"1578","1587":"1587","1597":"1597","estimated 1506":"umbes 1506","1585":"1585","estimated 1582":"umbes 1582","about 1597":"umbes 1597","1506":"1506","1505":"1505","1549":"1549","Broadwater, Sussex, England":"Broadwater, Sussex, England","England":"England","Sussex, England":"Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Rustington, Sussex, England":"Rustington, Sussex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1490–about 1597":"1490–noin 1597","1480–1578":"1480–1578","1506–1582":"1506–1582","1490–1597":"1490–1597","1582":"1582","1480":"1480","1490":"1490","1558":"1558","1578":"1578","1587":"1587","1597":"1597","estimated 1506":"